--options (-o)		Prints available application options (i.e ZFS, LUKS)
--version (-v)		Prints author, version, license information
--help    (-h)		Prints this help page

Usage:
You can run the program interactively by just starting the application:

# ./createInit

or you can run it directly by passing options to it. If you know the kernel and option you want,
you can pass it to the script like this:

# ./createInit 1 3.8.13-ALL
